        id "FSA-HDR 2.4C"
        check_description "In the event that a host device utilizes mobile code technologies, the host
            +b device shall provide the capability to enforce a security policy for the usage
            +b of mobile code technologies. The security policy shall allow, at a minimum, for
            +b each mobile code technology used on the host device, action to control the
            +b execution of mobile code based on the results of an integrity check prior to
            +b the code being executed."
        requirement_id "IEC 62443-4-2: HDR 2.4(c)"
        title "Mobile Code - Integrity Check"
        description "This requirement specifies that any mobile code used within the component must
            +b be subject to integrity checks to ensure its authenticity and that it has not
            +b been tampered with. The goal is to prevent unauthorized or malicious code from
            +b being executed within the industrial control system environment."
